The paper addresses the problem of automatic decompilation, which involves converting low-level code to a higher-level human-readable programming language. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including programming languages (cs.PL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer security (cs.CR), software engineering (cs.SE), and machine learning (cs.LG). Given that the paper proposes a novel approach based on neural machine translation, it is likely to be of interest to researchers in these areas.
